So the resource_classifier doesn't know about describe_instances as a root or enrichment operation for any canonical type. This means:

When describe_instances records arrive, the classifier can't classify them as enrichment for any asset, so they fall through and likely get treated as root operations instead, creating new assets. But the inventory scan shows "2664 root, 1018 enrichment" — so some operations ARE being classified as enrichment. Let me trace through the classifier logic to understand how this is actually happening.

